Original note from - https://civitai.com/models/1309065?modelVersionId=1845522

Last Frame of current Clip will be stored here in Preview Image node.


1.Right Click it and select "Send to workflow" / "Current Workflow"

2.New workflow will be created with last frame as new Input Image, so you can run a new generation based on last frame from previous clip


2-3 extensions are feasible, then quality starts to collapse. Make sure the last frame is a good one, as it will impact quality of further extended clips.

You still need to stitch the generated clips together with a video editor tool of your choice.


Since a new workflow will be created for each new clip, you can delete them afterwards or keep them to go back to any previous generation within a session. Alternatively you can just copy last frame image and paste it to Input Image to keep everything in the same worflow.

dpmpp_2 seems to be working fine.

I find uni_pc/simple to work well, other options are uni_pc/beta or euler_a/beta

Adding shift seems to add unwanted solid colors/graphics, so I've disabled it but sometimes it works.

Adjust end step and total steps as you like, try lowering the 1st CFG if you're getting any wierd outputs.

Original note from - https://civitai.com/models/1309065?modelVersionId=1845522

Own Prompt: 
Bypass Florence Prompt insertion by hitting the red Switch below the "Own Prompt" node in GUI to use your own Prompt. Florence will stil generate a caption. You can copy and adjust or just use your own prompt.

nodes.title: Prompt applied (Auto generated)
widgets_values: A serene anime girl with long black-pink hair and a flowing white-purple dress stands motionless in a moonlit flower field under a giant moon. Her eyes are always closed, never blinking, calm and peaceful. At the start the flower field glows with luminous red blossoms, and by the end it glows with luminous blue blossoms. Hair, ribbons, and dress sway softly in the wind, flower petals drift gently in the air. The color shift of the field is smooth and seamless, not a fade. The camera performs a smooth continuous dolly-in, physically moving forward from a wide view to a closer view of the girl, with natural parallax: foreground flowers enlarge and the moon shifts slightly in the background. This must look like real 3D camera motion, not fade, not dissolve, not crossfade.
